{"id":14880783,"mediaExerciseId":"e7207a81-2ed0-40ae-893b-9cb1816deb13","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612273,"groupTitle":"Concept Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":"3.5","sectionTitle":"Using Financial Statement Information","pageNumber":80,"solutions":[{"id":5904312,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine some uses and problems of a financial statement analysis. We are also required to determine what SIC codes are and its use. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define financial statements.\n\n**Financial statements** are formal records which show the financial activities and performance of a company. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd378a31605a289f/f20dd2c706c58a2d4fcba4202412d506/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd378a31605a289f/f20dd2c706c58a2d4fcba4202412d506/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"a. Financial analysis provides an understanding of the financial activities and performance of a company. This can also be used to make investments, for lending purposes and future financial decisions.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd378a31605a289f/50abe977acacd4a712d5d393f774894c/lateximg_large.png","width":1030},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd378a31605a289f/50abe977acacd4a712d5d393f774894c/lateximg.png","width":516}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"b. Financial statement analysis is management by exception because managers should focus on leading their company efficiently to focus on identifying and handling cases to recommend the best practice.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd378a31605a289f/5a389937598a8d4c315563e5a877b2b3/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd378a31605a289f/5a389937598a8d4c315563e5a877b2b3/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"c. Standard Industrial Classification or SIC codes are numeric codes which help companies to identify their existing and potential customers by industry. These are used to classify companies into specific industries for tax purposes.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd378a31605a289f/beb8a6e0370b1f7c8d85f1226ef841d9/lateximg_large.png","width":1019},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd378a31605a289f/beb8a6e0370b1f7c8d85f1226ef841d9/lateximg.png","width":511}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"d. Problems may arise with financial statement analysis due to lack of comparability between companies. Comparing two firms of the same industry may be difficult in terms of valuations and accounting policies. Financial statement analysis shows no indication of cause of changes, but business owners must dig deeper to determine the changes in ratios from period to period.  ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/95927cca02f48490fd37